64|ref=CITEREFLamsdellBraddyTetlie2010|first3=O. Erik|last3=Tetlie|issn=1478-0941}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Lamsdell|first=James C.|date=2012|title=Revised systematics of Palaeozoic 'horseshoe crabs' and the myth of monophyletic Xiphosura|journal=Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society|volume=167|issue=|pages=1\u201327|doi=10.1111/j.1096-3642.2012.00874.x|ref=CITEREFLamsdell2012}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Lamsdell|first=James C.|date=2013|title=Babes in the wood \u2013 a unique window into sea scorpion ontogeny|journal=BMC Evolutionary Biology|volume=13|issue=98|pages=98|doi=10.1186/1471-2148-13-98|ref=CITEREFLamsdellSelden2013|last2=Selden|first2=Paul|pmid=23663507|pmc=3679797}}\n*{{Cite book|title=Selectivity in the evolution of Palaeozoic arthropod groups, with focus on mass extinctions and radiations: a phylogenetic approach|last=Lamsdell|first=James C.|publisher=University of Kansas|year=2014|location=|pages=|ref=CITEREFLamsdell2014|url=https://kuscholarworks.ku.edu/handle/1808/14519}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Lamsdell|first=James C.|last2=Briggs|first2=Derek E. G.|date=2015|title=The oldest described eurypterid: a giant Middle Ordovician (Darriwilian) megalograptid from the Winneshiek Lagerst\u00e4tte of Iowa|journal=[[BMC Evolutionary Biology]]|volume=15|issue=169|pages=169|doi=10.1186/s12862-015-0443-9|ref=CITEREFLamsdellBriggsLiuWitzke2015|pmc=4556007|pmid=26324341|last3=Liu|last4=Witzke|first3=Huaibao|first4=Brian J.|last5=McKay|first5=Robert M.}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Lankester|first=E. Ray|date=1886|title=Professor Claus and the classification of the Arthropoda|journal=Annals and Magazine of Natural History|volume=17|issue=100|pages=364\u2013372|doi=10.1080/00222938609460154|ref=CITEREFLankester1886|url=https://zenodo.org/record/1615450}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=M'Coy|first=Frederick|date=1849|title=XLI.\u2014On the classification of some British fossil Crustacea, with notices of new forms in the University Collection at Cambridge|journal=Annals and Magazine of 